  <h2 id="what-air-ambulance-means">What Air Ambulance Coverage Means</h2>
  <p>
    Air ambulance coverage pays to transport you by aircraft for emergency medical care:
  </p>

  <h3>Types of Air Transport</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Air ambulance:</strong> Dedicated medical aircraft with equipment and staff</li>
    <li><strong>Helicopter evacuation:</strong> For remote or difficult-to-access locations</li>
    <li><strong>Medical escort:</strong> Medical professional accompanying you on commercial flight</li>
    <li><strong>Hospital-to-hospital transfer:</strong> Moving to a better-equipped facility</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>What's Typically Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Aircraft charter costs ($15,000-150,000+)</li>
    <li>Medical team and equipment on board</li>
    <li>Ground ambulance connections</li>
    <li>24/7 coordination and logistics</li>
    <li>Repatriation to home country</li>
    <li>Sometimes family travel to your bedside</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Why It's Expensive</h3>
  <p>
    Air ambulance flights cost $15,000-150,000+ depending on distance and aircraft type. International medical evacuations can exceed $100,000. Without insurance, you'd be responsible for this out-of-pocket.
  </p>

